                  <p>Sometimes a non-responsive touch control panel can be fixed by cleaning it thoroughly or performing a reset. If these steps donât work, it might require professional repair.</p>
                  
                  <b>Signs of a Malfunctioning Thermostat</b>
                  <ol>
                    <li>Inconsistent Cooking Temperatures: If your food is either undercooked or overcooked despite setting the correct temperature, the thermostat might not be regulating the heat properly.</li>
                    <li>Temperature Fluctuations: Noticeable fluctuations in oil temperature during cooking can indicate that the thermostat is not maintaining a consistent temperature.</li>
                    <li>Long Heat-Up Times: If the fryer takes an unusually long time to reach the desired temperature, it could be due to a faulty thermostat.</li>
                    <li>No Heat: If the fryer doesn't heat up at all, the thermostat might be completely broken or the heating element could be at fault.</li>
                    <li>Overheating: If the fryer continues to heat up beyond the set temperature and doesn't shut off, this is a clear sign of a malfunctioning thermostat.</li>
